task.summary: Add a field to store a list of subgraphs of the original graph, a new method: public void generateConceptSubgraphs()
Create a new class RulesSelectionFrame, and perform apply rules, this is the core
add a menu item “Select Rules”, add performActionSelectRules ( Graph theGraph) which invokes a wizard to select rules.
Fix bugs, add comments in match function

Add function in OperManager: public void addAugmentedGraphObjects (Graph currentGraph, Graph consequent) so that the consequent part of a rule now can be inferred (cloned) in CGs after applying rules. But the code looks ugly. May be we need to create another class to handle this.

Fix bugs in public void addAugmentedGraphObjects (Graph currentGraph, Graph consequent) arrow direction was wrong Also add a method called checkConsequentExisiting in OperManager, making sure that the consequent is not there in current graph before applying rules. So far it worked fine. Fix a bug in our famous match method, instead of using if n == null to tell there is not match, we add an int called isMatch We also modify the removeFromGraph method in Graph class.
Code review, add more comments, update DOC comments about Charger src.

1. Now, we can apply a rule ignoring coref links. More work needs to be done to relate consequent and antecedent concepts linked through coref. Add a new function: getArrowLinkedNodes() change addAugmentedGraphObjects() 2. I also added a field in class KnowledgeBase, it is intended to keep track of equivalent concepts, but we haven't done anything about it.

1. Now, we can apply a rule considering coref links. We successfully relate consequent and antecedent concepts linked through coref. 2.match() now returns the matched pattern between antecedent and the CG 3. Modified several functions: matchAll, addConsequent, addAugmentedGraphObjects() now accept one more parameter: the matched pattern returned by match()

Modified addAugmentedGraphObjects: now, we pick a node without coref link to start the copying process, and the duplicate concepts will not longer copied in the target CG. This is a great progress. Add a new method hasCorefEdge in GNode class Add a new method getEquivalentNodeInAntecedent in OperManger class.

THe flow is, we first match antecedent using type match, if true, we instantiate the consequent using the matched graph concepts and then match consequent using text label match, if not, we can add consequent to the graph. For example, if a graph has two sets of subgraphs with same structure, the rule will be applied twice instead of once. this is an improvement over previous versions.
Modified isConsequentExistent a lot, now we are match "exact" concepts (compare their text labels, not just type label) Add a new field in Rule, which keeps track of equivalent concepts from antecedent to consequent. Add a new method, getLinkedNodes() Add a new method, matchConsequent, which is very similar to match method. Modified parseRuleGraph which considers the coref info in a rule graph.

The flow is, we first match antecedent using type match, if true, we instantiate the consequent using the matched graph concepts and then match consequent using text label match, if not (that means we need to apply this rule), we can add consequent to the graph. For example, if a graph has two sets of subgraphs with same structure, the rule will be applied twice instead of once. this is an improvement over previous versions.
While the method addAugmentedGraphObjects is copying the instantiated consequent to the original CG, we need to in the consequent, look for coref linked concepts and concepts already exist in the original CG. We modified method addAugmentedGraphObjects to make sure already exisitent concepts will not be copied again.
Modified removeFromGraph method in Graph class, when a concept is removed, it is also removed from conceptHashStore and equivalentConceptHashStore (use iterator remove rather than arraylist remove to avoid current modification exception)
Modified insertInCharGerGraph in Graph class line 624 is changed, when a concept is added, we also add it into equivalentConceptHashStore, we are not adding it to the sameTypeConceptHashStore since that may cause the rule to be applied over and over during one inference action.
generateEquivalentConceptSubgraphs

Moving towards convert UML diagrams (xmi) to CGs. Initial achievements in this commit:
Add a new menu item, called UML2CGs, so our functions will no longer be mixed with the original Charger menus. Under this menu items, there are two sub items, one is select rules which was under Examine menu item; second one is UML to CGs conversion. This will start a new frame: Add a new frame, called UMLDiagramSelectionFrame, users can only select files with xmi as extension. Up to now, we have successfully import an xmi file, parse it and get the DOM structure, print UML classes, attributes, operations to the screen. Next step, we are going to convert this DOM file to real CGs.
